description: Backend standards for NestJS, tRPC, Mongoose, and Redis
globs: apps/api/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# API Standards (`apps/api`)

- Keep Nest modules cohesive: controller/entrypoints thin, business logic in services/use-cases.
- Prefer typed tRPC procedures for internal app API and validate inputs with Zod.
- Keep context creation explicit and side-effect free.

# Mongo and Redis

- Model Mongo collections by domain boundaries; avoid oversized documents.
- Use indexes for frequent filters/sorts and geo queries when relevant.
- Use Redis for cache/queue/rate-limit concerns; keep key naming explicit and scoped.
- Favor idempotent write paths for collaborative actions (votes, expenses, itinerary edits).

# Reliability

- Add health checks for core dependencies where practical.
- Fail fast on truly required configuration, but provide safe local defaults for DX.
- Keep lint/build green after each meaningful backend change.
